The paper discusses the design of a machine learning classifier using ambipolar carbon nanotube based field-effect transistors (AP-CNFETs). This falls under the category of emerging technologies (cs.ET) as it involves the use of a novel technology for computing. Additionally, the paper focuses on the use of AP-CNFETs for machine learning classification, which falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the design of the classifier using SPICE, which falls under the category of architecture (cs.AR) and digital circuits (cs.DC). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the classifier, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG).
